        <mxCell id="pub-contents-note" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontSize=9;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#555555;" value="• EC2 is in public subnet because it needs inbound HTTPS from users and outbound internet for OS updates &amp; npm.&lt;br&gt;• Access is restricted by the Security Group, not by subnet routing. Public subnet ≠ &quot;anyone can reach it&quot;." vertex="1" parent="public-subnet">
